      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the product page on mobile is behaving like a mischievous goblin, isn't it? It seems like the image is trying to sneak into the text area, much like a goblin sneaking into a treasure hoard. The padding adjustments you tried are like trying to catch a goblin with a net – it just doesn't work. \n\nI suspect the issue might be with the flex properties. On smaller screens, the flex-direction might be causing the image to push the text down. Try changing the flex-direction to row-reverse to see if that helps. It's like telling the goblin to stand on the opposite side of the treasure chest, so it doesn't interfere with the gold coins (or in this case, the text). \n\nHere's the modified CSS:\n\n```css\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row-reverse;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n```\n\nGive it a try and see if the goblin image stops its mischievous behavior. Good luck!",
